Privacy Policy - HSK 3 Mock Test & Flashcards

Effective date: March 10, 2026

HSK 3 Mock Test & Flashcards ("we", "our", or "the app") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what data the app processes, how it is used, and how users can contact us.

1) Scope

This Privacy Policy applies to the Android app HSK 3 Mock Test & Flashcards distributed through Google Play.

2) Data We Process

In the current version, we do not require users to create an account and we do not operate a developer-hosted user backend for learning progress.

The app primarily uses a local-first architecture and stores study-related data on your device, which may include:

- review counts
- streak information
- daily target settings
- font scale settings
- selected learning scope and onboarding preferences
- starred words and cram-list status
- mistake notebook items created from quiz or drill errors
- mock test history, recent attempts, accuracy summaries, and best score highlights
- local premium entitlement state after a successful Google Play purchase or restore

This data is used only to provide app features such as flashcards, mock tests, exam-prep drills, mistake review, progress tracking, and premium access on your device.

In the current version, this local study data is not uploaded to our own servers.

3) Data Sharing

We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties for advertising or profiling.

The app does not include third-party advertising SDKs in the current version.

If you choose to purchase a premium upgrade, payment processing is handled by Google Play and subject to Google's own terms and privacy practices.

4) Account and Login

The app does not require account registration or login in the current version.

5) Google Play Billing

The app may offer a one-time premium upgrade through Google Play Billing.

We do not directly process your payment card details. Google Play handles purchase transactions. The app only uses purchase status information necessary to unlock or restore premium access on your device.

6) Audio and Text-to-Speech

The app may use Android system text-to-speech (TTS) services for pronunciation playback.

TTS behavior depends on your device settings, installed voice packages, and any system-level services provided by your device or platform provider.

7) Data Retention and Deletion

Because the app is local-first in the current version, study progress and related settings are generally stored on your device.

You can delete this data at any time by:

- clearing app storage in Android settings, or
- uninstalling the app

Some device-level backup or restore behavior may also depend on Android system settings and device configuration.

8) Security

We use a local-first architecture in the current version and do not use a developer-hosted account system for study progress sync.

While no method of storage or transmission can be guaranteed 100% secure, we aim to limit data exposure by keeping core study data on the device in the current version.

9) Children’s Privacy

The app is designed for general language learners and is not primarily directed to children.

10) Policy Updates

We may update this Privacy Policy when app features or data practices change, for example if we later add cloud sync, analytics, ads, account features, or other new data flows.

When we update this Privacy Policy, we will revise the effective date above.

